---| EDITORIAL |-------------------------| DO YOU KNOW THE WAY TO SAN JOSE? |---
    ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯                           ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{FG Shine}Welcome to @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}@{FG Text}

Hello and welcome to the 9th issue of @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}.

I  don't  remember  a  month  with so many pieces of news! Let me count the most
important  ones:  the changes of position in Amiga Inc., the release of features
for  the  Amiga  OS  3.5, the announcement of Java 2 for Amiga (Daytona) and the
Phase 5's impressive development of a new PowerPC accelerator.

If  you  read  the  editorial  of the last issue perhaps you remember that I was
telling  you  "the  Gateway  people  are  quite  pissed nowadays with Amiga Inc.
delays".  Well,  this  rumour  has  been  finally confirmed with the decision of
Gateway:  Jim  Collas, a senior vicepresident of Gateway is now the president of
Amiga.  This means that (finally) Amiga has the full support of Gateway, and the
parent company has been the responsible of the delays (and everybody was blaming
Jeff).

This  move has got several consequences: Amiga Inc. has moved to San Diego, near
Silicon  Valley,  and finally they are looking for people to work in AmigaSoft 4
and 5. So, if you are interested, perhaps you could apply.

And  what tabout the OS3.5? Now it is confirmed that Haage&Partner and Petro has
taken  the  control  of  its  development, and although the RTG and RTA has been
removed  form  the  list of features, they are doing their best. And this update
could not be the last revision of the Amiga OS.

There  is  a  technology  with was missing in this great OS: Java. There is some
efforts,  like  Kaffe,  but  Holger  Kruse  (author  of Miami) has announced the
development  of  Daytona,  finally  Java 2 for Amiga... and free of charge, both
for users and developers.

And last, but not least, the big surprise of the month. If you read usually this
editorial,  you  already  know my worries abouth the silence of Phase 5. I would
bet  they  were  leaving  the  Amiga  World,  but  fortunately I was wrong. This
Cyberstorm G3/G4 is the dream of every Amiga owner.

Anyway  I  see two big problems: they need 1,000 preorder (which is not going to
be  easy to get), and the time frame. A release for the end of the year could be
too  late.  There  are  people who want/need the PowerPC power now (e.g. me ;-))
and  I  can  wait  for so  long. Other people have PowerUp cards, and taken into
account  the  small  size  of the market, it is not going to be easy to sell the
CyberstormPPC/CybervisionPPC in the second hand market.

Remember to visit the @{B}SAUG-news @{UB}website, which is located in:

         @{B}www.saug.com/eng/news.html@{UB}

or you can visit its mirrors located in:

         @{B}soporte.databasedm.es/amiga/sau/news.html@{UB}

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

         @{I}angel@saug.org @{UI}

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
