@node not01 "BLACKIRC 1.0 IS NOW AVAILABLE"

@{B}BLACKIRC 1.0 @{UB}IS NOW AVAILABLE
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE@{UI}

The new IRC-Client @{B}BlackIRC @{UB}is now available in its first full release.

As  promised  last  year,  we  now  bring  the major update for @{B}BlackIRC@{UB}. It now
supports  all  common  IRC-standards (CTCP, DCC, etc.). The most needed feature,
textwrapping,  was also added now and support for colored text is included, too.
In order to enable all the talented @{B}ARexx@{UB}-coders among the @{B}AMIGA@{UB}-users, @{B}BlackIRC@{UB}
now  also features an @{B}ARexx@{UB}-port and already has some nice (and funny :) scripts
included.  Security  is  essential on the internet and therefore @{B}BlackIRC @{UB}is the
first  @{B}Amiga@{UB}-Client  that  has CTCP-Flood-protection and SPAM-filtering INBUILT.
The  price  still  is 20 DEM/13 USD/10 EURO and if you want @{B}BlackIRC @{UB}to make the
next  great  step  forward,  you  should  register  now.  For  more information,
screenshots   and   a   downloadable   demoversion,   don`t   miss  our  website
(@{B}innovative.in-tec.de@{UB}).

Changes since 0.91prerelease / new features of V1.0 are:
  * updated fsgfx.library to V44
  * added @{B}ARexx@{UB}-interface and some example scripts including:
      - Friendlybot.birx: A friendly bot for friendly people
      - Grab.birx:  Example  for CTCP-Server: Grab your current screen on demand
        and send it via DCC to a user. This example was written by @{I}Phil Price@{UI}.
  * added @{B}ARexx@{UB}-popup-button
  * added Alias-Support
  * added CTCP-server allowing to do the following:
      - reply text
      - execute a CLI command
      - start an @{B}ARexx@{UB}-script
      - Play a sound
      - Send a file
      - XDCC Server
      - combine all these actions
  * added input-buffer. Scrolling in it arrow up and arrow down is possible now.
  * rewrote  whole  UserOP-stuff.  Now  up to 36 buttons are possible and easily
    configurable!
  * did some improvement to the GUI
  * added About-Win for @{I}Stuntzi @{UI};-)
  * added @{B}MUI@{UB}-Settingsbutton
  * added some useful buttons and one display to the private chat windows
  * added CTCP-Flood-Protection
  * @{B}BlackIRC@{UB}`s window can now be scaled a lot smaller
  * Added Event-Handler
      - add sounds to events
      - highlight text
      - execute Rexx-scripts
      - execute a program
      - add text to hotkeys (F1-F10)!
  * CHAT-LISTVIEWS NOW USING NList!!
      - Auto Text-Wrapping
      - Clipboard-Support
      - Colored Text-Support
      - Enhanced support for other text-flags
  * Added XDCC-Server
      - have your own XDCC-server on IRC!
      - Connect several files to one PACK-ID
      - With HELP for the users of your service
      - Give the XDCC-server ANY CTCP-command you want!
      - Ability to switch the inbuilt server off and use the another one.
  * removed some major bugs
  * @{B}Windows  95@{UB}®  (ugly  word)  Client  for  the  new videoconferencing standard
    available from our website (@{B}innovative.in-tec.de@{UB})

We wish you a lot of fun with the new version

