@node not03 "THE DEVELOPMENT OF LUNATIC ISLES HAS BEEN CANCELLED"

THE DEVELOPMENT OF @{B}LUNATIC ISLES @{UB}HAS BEEN CANCELLED
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{B}Sanios  Software @{UB} is  a  new  development  team for @{B}Amiga @{UB}which intended to port
several  games  to  the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. One of them was @{B}Guts'n'Garters in DNA Danger@{UB}, but
@{B}Ocean Software @{UB}has finally denied its conversion to the @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

Something  similar  has  happened  with  @{B}Lunatic  Isles@{UB},  a children's isometric
platform game. They succeed in licensing this game, but its development has been
cancelled due to a complete lack of support for the project. It seems that there
is absolutely no support in the @{B}Amiga @{UB}market for a game of this type.

Anyway, @{B}Sanios @{UB}have gone ahead and started to create their own game from scratch
entitled  @{B}Mage  Wars@{UB}. It brings those old "Dungeon and Dragon&quot games back to
life, incorporating @{B}AGA @{UB}graphics with a real time or turn based engine (actually
you choose how you want to play).

In  this game, as a Mage (sometimes known as a wizard) you will have to traverse
a  vast  land-scape on your quest and gain experience and power as you go along.
There  are  hundreds  of  unique items to be found that will both aid and hinder
your  quest.  Magic  Spells  by  the  bucket  load and plenty of interesting and
dangerous  characters.  The  graphics  are being done by the people behind @{B}Sixth
Sense  Investigations@{UB},  so  @{B}Mage  Wars @{UB} could  be a hit amongst the role playing
comunity.  One  of  the  many  features  included in @{B}Mage Wars @{UB}is the ability to
create  your  own  character from scratch. It will be possible to elaborate your
own  history  and  to  include your own graphics and sound. @{B}Mage Wars @{UB}is due for
release late this year.

On  the  other  hand,  @{B}Sanios @{UB} are  looking  for creative ideas to go into their
current  and  future  games.  If you have a story line or some neat features you
feel  could  work  in their games you can drop a line by mailing @{I}Dan Stephens @{UI}at
@{I}dans@ion.com.au@{UI}.

Also, they are currently looking for a WebMaster and a 3D programmer. If you are
interested  in  this, e-mail @{I}Dan @{UI}at the same adress. For more information, visit
the @{B}Sanios Software @{UB}site at @{B}sanios.ion.tm@{UB}.
