@node not04 "AMIGA ANNOUNCES NEW PRESIDENT AND FAST-TRACK DEVELOPMENT PLANS"

@{B}AMIGA @{UB}ANNOUNCES NEW PRESIDENT AND FAST-TRACK DEVELOPMENT PLANS
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
SAN  DIEGO,  Calif.  - February 26, 1999 - In a series of meetings in San Diego,
representatives  of  @{B}Amiga  Inc. @{UB} and  @{B}Amiga International @{UB}met to hammer out the
details of technical, strategic and marketing plans which will see the launch of
a  range  of  new @{B}Amiga@{UB}-based computers for the next millennium. The company has
relocated  its  headquarters  to San Diego and @{I}Jim Collas @{UI}will be serving as the
new president of @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

@{I}"@{B}Amiga @{UB} is  an  amazing  opportunity  that we must act on now or it will be lost
forever," @{UI} said  @{I}Collas@{UI}.  @{I}"The  @{B}Amiga@{UB}®  platform  is  ideal  for Internet-ready,
consumer-oriented digital appliances of the future. The @{B}Amiga @{UB}name is associated
the  world  over  with user-friendly, low cost, powerful computing. We will take
this  philosophy  into  the  next  generation,  enabling products from hand held
Internet  appliances  to  high-end  graphics computers that help the user rather
than frustrate them."@{UI}

@{I}Collas@{UI},  formerly  a  senior vice president for @{B}Amiga@{UB}'s parent company, @{B}Gateway@{UB},
will  be  running  @{B}Amiga @{UB} as  a wholly independent subsidiary operation and will
integrate  @{B}Amiga  Inc. @{UB} and  @{B}Amiga  International @{UB} under the new @{B}Amiga @{UB}corporate
structure.  His  leadership  will  allow  the  company to step up a fast - track
development program that is currently underway.

@{B}Amiga @{UB} is  planning  to launch next generation products worldwide before the New
Year.  They will be announcing detailed product plans and introducing several of
their  strategic  partners  over the summer. Products currently targeted for the
initial  launch  are a development system, an Internet appliance, and a low cost
home  computer  in the tradition of the @{B}Amiga A500 @{UB}that dominated home computing
in the late eighties and early nineties. The developers system will be available
with a software development suite for low cost development on the new platform.

@{I}Jeff  Schindler@{UI},  in  charge  of product strategy for @{B}Amiga@{UB}, is planning the new
@{B}Amiga @{UB} product  line. @{I}"The @{B}Amiga @{UB}community has been doing incredible things on a
platform  which  hasn't  had an official update in eight years," @{UI}said @{I}Schindler@{UI}.
@{I}"They deserve a system which lets them show off their talents."@{UI}

@{B}Amiga@{UB}'s  administrative  center  in  San Diego will shortly be complemented by a
software  development  center  under  the leadership of Dr. @{I}Allan Havemose@{UI}, vice
president  of Engineering for @{B}Amiga@{UB}, in San Jose, California. The Silicon Valley
team  will  be  rapidly expanded over the coming months to develop revolutionary
@{B}Amiga @{UB} multimedia  layers  over the real-time @{B}Neutrino OS @{UB}core from @{B}QNX Software
Systems Ltd@{UB}.

@{I}Petro Tyschtschenko @{UI}will continue on as managing director of @{B}Amiga International@{UB}
and  will  also  play  a  critical  role  in guiding the current @{B}Amiga @{UB}community
through the transition to the new @{B}Amiga @{UB}architecture. @{I}"The new @{B}Amiga @{UB}plans are a
rebirth for @{B}Amiga @{UB}and an exciting journey into the future," @{UI}said @{I}Tyschtschenko@{UI}.

For   further   information  on  @{B}Amiga @{UB} and  @{B}Amiga @{UB} products,  please  refer  to
@{B}www.amiga.com @{UB}and @{B}www.amiga.de@{UB}.
