@node not15 "OPEN LETTER TO THE AMIGA COMMUNITY"

OPEN LETTER TO THE @{B}AMIGA @{UB}COMMUNITY
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
March 2, 1999

February 8, 1999 - a historical day.

This  day  reminded  me  of  the spirit of 1985, when @{B}Amiga @{UB}was presented to the
world public in New York.

This time a vision is born: Making computers a natural part of everyday life.

It is almost 2 years ago, since the take over by @{B}Gateway@{UB}. Many people know me as
an  impatient  man and you may anticipate how difficult the period from March 97
to  February  8, 1999 was. A time of low communication with the @{B}Amiga @{UB}community,
low public relations and low information about visions, missions and goals.

But my dear Amigans, I can reassure you the ray of hope will become a bright sun
within  the  next  6  month.  The  @{B}Amiga @{UB} will  be  lead to the future under the
technical experienced management of an absolute professional. @{I}Jim Collas@{UI}, Senior
Vice  President Product Development & Management of @{B}Gateway, Inc. @{UB}has decided to
modify  his  position and to work for @{B}Amiga @{UB}only. To reach all our goals, I will
work on his side and support him with all my energy.

@{B}Our mission is:@{UB}

To  create  a  revolutionary  and  compelling systems architecture and operating
environment  for  multimedia  computers and digital information appliances which
can  easily  be  imbedded into consumer computing devices and enables innovative
Internet services.

Without  talk  big,  I  can  tell  you that in the middle of November 99 we will
launch the new @{B}Amiga @{UB}systems architecture and operation environment.

For  this  purpose we will organize press conferences to inform the public about
our  goals  and  directions.  Besides  the new and revolutionary @{B}Amiga @{UB}Operating
System  we  are  working  on our existing platform to present the upgrade @{B}3.5 @{UB}as
soon as possible

First  detailed  information  will  be  presented in St. Louis, USA (March 12. -
14.).  We hope to be in the position to sell the first Operating System upgrades
@{B}3.5 @{UB} in  summer 99. The German company @{B}Haage & Partner @{UB}and myself will take care
about this project.

@{B}AMIGA  International, Inc. @{UB}and @{B}Amiga, Inc. @{UB}will conquer as one team the computer
world;  under  the management of @{I}Jim Collas @{UI}- and you my dear Amigans, will be a
part of it.

Help us performing our goals.

@{I}Jim  Collas @{UI} will  inform you within the next days about the organization, plans
and goals of our company.

A  very  exciting  time  is coming and it is for me and my staff a honor to be a
part  of a new computer generation as pioneer and to pave the way for the future
just like it was at @{B}Commodore@{UB}.

Long live our beloved @{B}Amiga @{UB}and our community

Yours
@{I}Petro Tyschtschenko@{UI}
2.March 1999
