@node not38 "ANNOUNCEMENT: THE MIDWEST AMIGA EXPOSITION"

ANNOUNCEMENT: @{B}THE MIDWEST AMIGA EXPOSITION@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE@{UI}

From: @{I}Dave Pearce @{UI}@{I}dpearce@infinet.com@{UI}@{UI}
Organization: @{B}The Amiga Central Ohio Network@{UB}
Date: March 25th, 1999

To all @{B}Amiga @{UB}supporters:

Many of you have emailed us asking whether or not the @{B}Amiga Central Ohio Network@{UB}
will  produce the @{B}Midwest Amiga Exposition @{UB}for 1999. At this time we will not be
producing a show for 1999.

Our  show  was  created by everyday users for the sole purpose of supporting the
@{B}Amiga @{UB} during  some  of it's roughest times. In 1996, when we started our event,
most  other  events  had  closed  their  doors  and  an  important role was left
unfulfilled.  We  felt  we  needed  to support a diminishing market during those
times for other users and more importantly, developers.

While  some  might  argue,  we  believe we had a small role in helping the @{B}Amiga@{UB}
trade  show  market in the U.S. become active again. @{B}Amiga @{UB}trade events are once
again  gaining  popularity  and  increasing  in size, so rather than compete for
exhibitors  and  attendees,  we  have  decided  it is time to step aside and let
others continue on.

The  @{B}Amiga @{UB} situation  is  currently  more  positive than in the past and we are
excited  about  the  recent  developments at @{B}Amiga Inc@{UB}. We will not rule out the
possibility  of bringing back the @{B}Midwest Amiga Exposition @{UB}in the years to come,
but  for  now,  we  are  confident  that  @{B}Amiga @{UB} trade  shows in the U.S. are in
competent and capable hands.

We  have put together a scrapbook from each year of the @{B}Midwest Amiga Exposition@{UB}
and  we  encourage  you to visit our web site at @{B}www.amicon.org/mae.html @{UB}and see
what it was like to be there.

There are simply too many people to thank in the end for what has become for us,
a  personal  chapter  in  the history of the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. Our debt of gratitude to the
@{B}Amiga @{UB}community and to the developers that stuck it out is too large to measure.

Sincerely,

@{I}David Pearce@{UI}
President
@{B}The Amiga Central Ohio Network@{UB}
