@node not48 "PHASE 5 DIGITAL PRODUCTS INTRODUCES THE CYBERSTORM G3/G4"

@{B}PHASE 5 DIGITAL PRODUCTS @{UB}INTRODUCES THE @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE@{UI}

Oberursel,  March  19,  1999:  Once  again  @{B}phase 5 digital products @{UB}is happy to
announce  a  groundbreaking  new development, which will represent an extract of
@{B}phase 5@{UB}'s leading-edge technologies and the many years of expertise in designing
upgrade  products  for  @{B}Amiga @{UB} computers.  After  a  long time of evaluating the
market,  we  have  decided  to  support the existing @{B}Amiga @{UB}user base and the new
developments  at  @{B}Amiga  Inc. @{UB} with  a next generation product, which will offer
highest  performance,  future  compatibility and a bridge to industry standards.
This  product  will  be  a powerful @{B}PPC @{UB}accelerator for @{B}A3000@{UB}/@{B}A4000 @{UB}systems (and
other @{B}Amiga @{UB}systems expanded with an @{B}A4000 @{UB}compatible CPU slot) and the upcoming
@{B}Amiga OS 3.5@{UB}, as well as future versions of the @{B}Amiga OS@{UB}.

The  new  accelerator,  the  @{B}CYBERSTORM  G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB} board,  is  a pure @{B}PowerPC@{UB}-based
processor  card.  It  will  ship  with a fast @{B}PowerPC750 @{UB}or @{B}PowerPC7400 @{UB}(@{B}G4 @{UB}with
@{B}Altivec@{UB}), which is installed in a @{B}ZIF @{UB}socket. This @{B}ZIF @{UB}socket is fully compliant
with  the  @{B}Interposer @{UB} standard  from  @{B}IBM @{UB} and  @{B}Motorola@{UB}, which is also used in
@{B}PowerMac@{UB}s  and other systems, what will allow easy upgrading, if required by the
user  in  the future. In the base version with a 400MHz @{B}PowerPC750 @{UB}processor and
1MB  backside  Cache  @  200MHz, the @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}will provide an impressing
peak  performance of up to 19.2 SPECint95 and 13.1 SPECfp95 (source: @{B}IBM @{UB}website
03/18/99).  In  real-world  applications,  this  allows  incredible  application
performance, which is estimated to reach 15 -20 times the performance of a 50MHz
@{B}68060 @{UB} processor  (with native @{B}PowerPC @{UB}coded or @{B}PowerPC @{UB}optimized applications).
The @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}will use standard @{B}SDRAM @{UB}running at 100MHz, providing a peak
memory transfer rate of 582 MB/s, and has two @{B}DIMM @{UB}sockets which will support up
to  1 GB main memory. An on-board @{B}PCI 2.1 @{UB}interface will allow the connection of
all  kind  of  industry  standard devices and cards. The on-board @{B}Flash ROM @{UB}with
512kB  size  can  be  used  to install software necessary for system-startup and
other  functionalities.  By  default,  this  @{B}Flash ROM @{UB}will only contain a basic
boot-strap  functionality (hardware write protected) which will allow to install
any  kind  of  system  software  from  disks;  this  functionality will be fully
documented and freely available to everybody.

By it's design concept, the @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}is the perfect solution for running
native @{B}PowerPC @{UB}coded Operating Systems as well as emulated @{B}68k OS @{UB}segments. As a
processor  card which fits into the @{B}A4000 @{UB}compatible fast slot, it allows to run
100%   native  @{B}PowerPC @{UB} code,  and  has  full  access  to  all  system  hardware
functionalities  and  interrupts which is not the case with add-ons that are not
installed  in  the  fast slot, but e.g. in a @{B}Zorro @{UB}slot. With it's ability to be
the  master  system  CPU,  the  @{B}PowerPC @{UB}on the @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}does not need an
additional  @{B}68k @{UB} processor  which  is  the  case  in  other  designs. Beside the
technical advantages of this approach, it offers the user the opportunity to e g
sell  an  existing @{B}68060 @{UB}processor card in the second-hand market, thus lowering
the cost of the upgrade to the @{B}PowerPC G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}generation.

@{B}phase  5  digital  products @{UB} will  NOT built or deliver any software or hardware
add-ons  for  the  @{B}CYBERSTORM  G3@{UB}/@{B}G4@{UB}. The @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}will be open to third
party developers in a wide way:
  * Software  support will be realized with the new developments from @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB}
    and  @{B}Haage&Partner@{UB},  especially  with  the upcoming @{B}Amiga OS3.5 @{UB}with @{B}PowerPC@{UB}
    support,  and  upcoming  @{B}68k @{UB}emulator products. Additionally, the @{B}CYBERSTORM
    G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB} is perfectly suited for the implementation of other Operating Systems
    such as @{B}Linux@{UB}, which have already been realized on earlier @{B}PowerUp @{UB}boards.
  * For   hardware  add-ons,  the  implemented  @{B}PCI  2.1 @{UB} interface  will  allow
    third-party  vendors to design @{B}PCI @{UB}bus backplanes, and write drivers for any
    common  @{B}PCI @{UB} card  on  the  market. The interface is implemented as a single
    connector,  to  which  other  vendors  can  connects  e.g.  @{B}PCI @{UB}cards or @{B}PCI@{UB}
    backplanes, or design a physical link to @{B}PCI @{UB}slots on bus expansion boards.

However,  due  to the current market status, we can only justify the realization
of  this  project with a significant number of preorders. We will therefore have
to  collect  a  total  of  1,000  orders  from customers (end users, dealers, or
distributors).  For each of these orders, we will also ask for a down-payment of
DM  250,  which  will  be  collected  on  a notary account and will only be made
available  to  us  at  the  time  we deliver the @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}product to the
customers. This gives security to all customers who want to support this exiting
new  project  and  get stunning @{B}G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}performance for their @{B}Amiga@{UB}, and will give
security to us when we make the necessary investments.
@{I}What will be the cost of this product, and are there benefits for preordering?@{UI}

The regular list price for the @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4@{UB}, including
  * the  @{B}CYBERSTORM  G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB} mainboard  with  an  @{B}Interposer ZIF @{UB}socket for @{B}G3@{UB}/@{B}G4@{UB}
    processor  modules, 2 SDRAM DIMM sockets for up to 1 GB memory, 512 kB @{B}Flash
    ROM @{UB} for  system  software  (system software not provided with the board), a
    fully  implemented  @{B}PCI 2.1 @{UB}interface with one connector (for @{B}PCI @{UB}backplanes
    provided by third party vendors)
  * one  @{B}G3 @{UB}CPU module, with a @{B}PowerPC750 @{UB}processor with 400MHz and one Megabyte
    Backside Cache with 200MHz clock rate
will  be  DM  1,995  plus  local taxes (in Germany: DM 2.299,- incl. MwSt). This
price is based on the current price projections for components and parts for the
3rd quarter 1999, and will be updated whenever major components such as the CPUs
fall in price.

A  price  for  a  @{B}CYBERSTORM  G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}model with the new @{B}XPC7400 @{UB}(@{B}G4 @{UB}with @{B}Altivec@{UB})
processor  is  not  yet  determined, and will depend on the pricing of these new
processors.  As  soon  as we have these pricings, we will determine a list price
for this product.

For those Amigans who are ready to support this major technological step forward
by placing one of the necessary preorders, we offer a special benefit: Customers
who  are  ready  to  order  this  board  in advance, at the conditions mentioned
herein,  will  get this stunning product for a special discounted preorder price
of  DM  1,750  plus  local  taxes, including world-wide free delivery by economy
postal  service.  And  even  more:  If  the  regular list price drops before the
preordered  @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}boards start to ship, the discounted preorder price
will be reduced by the same amount.

@{I}How will the whole project proceed, and be finalized?@{UI}

First  of  all,  we  will  now  be  looking forward to the response of the @{B}Amiga@{UB}
community  to  this project. The basic concepts of the @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4@{UB}, as well
as  major  parts of the design (such as the @{B}SDRAM @{UB}controller and the @{B}PCI @{UB}bridge)
have  been  developed  at  @{B}phase  5  digital  products @{UB} during the past year, as
building  blocks  of other projects that we are working on; in other words, most
of the product is already "in the drawer". From the day we can make the decision
to  start  the  project  finalization, we estimate roughly four months until the
product  can  be  shipped  to  the  customers. Therefore, the shipping date will
largely depend on the time which we need to collect the preorders.

The project has four stages:
  * @{I}Announcement and preorder phase.@{UI}

    We  now  collect  preorders  from  customers all over the world. Please only
    place  a  preorder  -  which  is not yet legally binding - if you are really
    ready  to  buy  the  @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4@{UB}, and if you are ready to later pay the
    prepayment.  If many users place preorders now, but then cancel or refuse to
    prepay,  this  will  hurt  the  project  flow  significantly. If you are not
    definitely interested in this stunning new technology, please don't place an
    order.

  * @{I}Notification phase.@{UI}

    Once  we  have  received  the  necessary  1,000  preorders - the sooner, the
    better,  of course - we will open the notary account, and send notifications
    to  all customers which will include a proforma invoice and the terms of the
    contract,  as well as information about the usage of the prepayments. At the
    same  time,  we  will  also  release updated product information and updated
    pricing,  if  available.  All  customers will be asked to pay the prepayment
    with 3 weeks to the notary account.

    @{I}Important@{UI}:  The prepaid amounts will not become available to @{B}phase 5 digital
    products @{UB} before  we  actually  ship  the  @{B}CYBERSTORM  G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB} boards  to the
    customers  who  have  ordered.  If  we  fail to deliver the product within a
    certain   time  from  date  of  notification,  the  prepaid  money  will  be
    reimbursed. The prepaid money will not be reimbursed if the customer cancels
    his order for any reason.

  * @{I}Development phase.@{UI}

    Design  finalization  and verification, including rapid prototyping and full
    in-system  test  will require appx. 3 months. During this time, we will also
    work   in   close  contact  with  other  developers,  and  support  software
    development on the new boards.

  * @{I}Release & Shipment@{UI}

    Once  the  @{B}CYBERSTORM  G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}is released for production, we will go into the
    assembly,  and  start  to fullfill the preorders. The first boards will ship
    appx.  4  weeks  after  the  start  of  the production. We will fullfill the
    preorders  in  the  order  we  have  received  them. After the preorders are
    fullfilled,  we  will decide if we continue to built @{B}CYBERSTORM G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}boards
    for  the  regular  market,  what will depend on the market situation and the
    demand forecasts at this time.

If  you  want to take part in this stunning new development for the @{B}AMIGA@{UB}, which
finally  will bring the latest @{B}G3@{UB}/@{B}G4 @{UB}technology to the @{B}AMIGA @{UB}and support the new
developments  by  @{B}AMIGA  Inc. @{UB} and  their partners, then go ahead and @{B}PLACE YOUR
CYBERSTORM G3/G4 PREORDER NOW!@{UB}
