@node art01 "NICE TO BE BACK AGAIN - BY FLEECY MOSS"
   
NICE TO BE BACK AGAIN - BY @{I}FLEECY MOSS @{UI}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Hey there 8-)

First  of  all,  apologies  for  my  long  absence.  I  have been working in the
background on @{B}Amiga @{UB}issues, and trying to stay in touch, but employment, family,
sickness  and  just  pure  plain  being knackered have kept me apart for far too
long.

I  am  writing this mail because there are some pretty horrendous rumours flying
around  about  what  I  have and have not said, about how I hate ppl, am issuing
death  threats,  will work for @{B}MS@{UB}, have breast implants, and a lot of other crap
which is fit only for a Hollywood 'D' movie.

I  am  writing  some regular columns for @{B}Amazing @{UB}now, a great magazine, that has
kindly  given  me a home, and which has brought both @{I}Fletcher Haug @{UI}and @{I}Don Hicks
@{UI}together,  two  of  the  brightest  and  best  in  @{B}Amiga  @{UB}journalism. We are all
determined  to  provide  the  best  possible home for the @{B}Amiga @{UB}community, past,
present  and  future,  or at least to the US portion of the community - until we
get foreign distributors anyway.

I  have  a  big article coming up about my thoughts re the @{I}Collas @{UI}PR, so I don't
want  to  reveal  too  much,  but  hearing that I had made death threats against
Schindler has sort of forced my hand.

For the record

  * I am ECSTATIC that @{I}Collas @{UI}has taken charge. To me it shows
      - that @{B}Gateway @{UB}have finally gotten serious about the @{B}Amiga@{UB}
      - that @{B}Amiga @{UB}now has a very talented leader with a proven track record for
        getting  things  done.  He  brings experience, industry wide respect and
        contacts,  and a direct line to the very top of @{B}Gateway@{UB}, because that is
        were he has been for the past few years.
    It  is great news that @{I}Havemose @{UI}has been taken on. He is a very talented and
    determined task manager and once things start moving, he is exactly the sort
    of person I would chose to run and push a technical project team.

  * I  would  like  to  see  a  public announcement about and commitment to @{I}Bill
    McEwen@{UI}. Whilst not coming from the @{B}Amiga @{UB}community, he has worked tirelessly
    behind the scenes to promote and inform the @{B}Amiga @{UB}community, irrespective of
    how  the  @{B}Amiga  @{UB}community  may  have received the end result. A few ppl are
    pissed  at  @{I}Bill@{UI},  but you should never shoot the postman when he brings you
    bad news, or worse, no news.

  * The  announcement  is  a  start. It does make vague cotton wool promises but
    also promises 2 products. I hope that after the empty promises of the last 2
    years,  @{I}Collas  @{UI}understands that if he says there will be product, there had
    better  be  product.  I  also  caution  the  community,  and  this is just a
    reiteration of what many have said since the term Digital Convergence raised
    its  head, that @{B}Amiga Inc @{UB}may not, and do not have to go in a direction that
    the  community  requires.  Like  it or not (and I do), there is a revolution
    coming  in  digital  information markets, and that is where @{B}Amiga Inc @{UB}should
    head, to give @{B}Amiga @{UB}the success it finally deserves. If @{B}Collas@{UB}'s strategy is
    one  of  produce and licence, then hopefully, there will be big opportunites
    for  third  parties  to  target  the many markets our community can provide,
    whether  Hardware,  with  @{B}Index@{UB}, @{B}DKB@{UB}, @{B}Metabox@{UB}, @{B}ACT@{UB}, @{B}Villagetronic @{UB}and @{B}P5@{UB}, or
    SW,   with   @{I}Paul   Nolan@{UI},   @{B}H&P@{UB},   @{B}NordicGlobal@{UB},  @{B}Finale@{UB},  @{B}Amitrix@{UB},  @{B}Vapor@{UB},
    @{B}Omnipresence@{UB},  @{B}Thule@{UB},  @{B}Digita@{UB},  @{B}Final Writer@{UB}, @{B}Cloanto@{UB}, the hundreds of games
    developers,  the thousands of shareware. We have a new man, one I have a lot
    of faith in, and respect for - of course, only time will tell - as always.

  * @{I}Schindler@{UI}. I have no personal issues with @{I}Schindler@{UI}. I had a lot of fun with
    him.  He  has  a great wife and kids and really is a nice guy. Ppl can, have
    and  will  make their own judgements relating to the efforts of the last two
    years,  his  performance  and business acumen. @{I}Collas @{UI}hasn't got where he is
    today  without  being  a good judge of character, and if he is the new boss,
    then  he  will make the calls as he sees them. My position is already known.
    However,  the  @{B}Amiga  @{UB}has  always  been, and rightly so, bigger than any one
    person.  We  need  to look to the future, ensure that @{I}Collas @{UI}knows the views
    and opinions of the community, and that we come to work together. Anyone who
    say  him  at  the press conference in London knows that he is a man who will
    talk,  will listen and will rethink his position. This is a man with whom we
    can  hopefully do business. There is a lot of anger at how the community has
    been  treated  but  we  have  to  make  sure we don't blow an opportunity to
    influence  the  future by continuing to stay angry. @{I}Collas @{UI}could have stayed
    more  than  comfortably off at the highest level of @{B}Gateway@{UB}, but he has seen
    something  worth pursuing. We have to make sure that he has the good company
    of the community along with him.

  * @{I}McEwen  @{UI}and  I  are  not  getting  married. Despite my fondness for "Nuclear
    wings"  @{I}Bill@{UI},  I am too fond of @{I}Elspeth @{UI}and the kids. Getting to know him is
    one  of  the  best  things  that  happened to me at @{B}Amiga Inc@{UB}, and the @{B}Amiga
    @{UB}community  has  a  real  friend  in  him.  Hell, he is so much a part of the
    community  that @{I}Cooksey @{UI}has sent him over 100 mails - if that isn't official
    membership material, then I don't know what is.

In  short,  I  am very happy that @{I}Collas @{UI}is now in charge, @{I}Havemose @{UI}is full time
and  we  finally  have some momentum. St Louis will be a big test, and I hope we
will not have a repeat of the "no news" of the past. There are many issues to be
resolved,  the  status  of  the  classic,  developer  support,  user evangelism,
strategic and product partners, licencing, how @{B}QNX @{UB}fits into the picture

these  are  issues  that  have  been  waiting 2 years to be solved, I sense that
someone  as  smart  as  @{I}Collas @{UI}has proved himself to be in the past will address
them all, and more.

For  the  first  time  in  a long time I think there may be a final crack in the
darkness that has surrounded us for the past five years.

.....and if any wacky rumours start flying, please just ask me.

Don't  forget,  to  see  my  full  feelings  about the @{I}Collas @{UI}PR, @{I}McEwen@{UI}'s brief
flirtation  with wigs, the future, plus @{I}Fletcher @{UI}"Are you looking at me?" @{I}Haug@{UI}'s
incisive  editorial  and  Uncle @{I}Don@{UI}'s view of the new faces at @{B}Amiga Inc@{UB}, steal,
teleport,  smuggle,  swim  the  Atlantic, or simply buy @{B}Amazing Amiga@{UB}... because
@{B}Amazing @{UB}ppl write for it, and @{B}Amazing @{UB}ppl read it.

...now  I couldn't have made that last line up if I drank American beer, could I
;-)

Have a nice K 8-)
~~~

@{UI}fleecy moss @{UI}  *--* myself, my community, my world *--* husband/father
 @{B}KOSH@{UB}an (@{B}Kommunity Operating System & Hardware@{UB}) @{B}http://www.kosh.net@{UB}
